text:
(1)
Central Park: The Lake, view south from the northern end, showing the midtown skyline between Fifth and Eighth Avenues, from
the Hotel Plaza to the General Motors Building.
June 28, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, four years later. The gigantic R. C. A. Building, at
Radio City, has been added to the skyline.
June 24, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Harlem Mere.
